#\#CIF_2.0
# Tests: repeated loop key.
# The ATOM_SITE loop has five rows indexed by the explicitly
# given _atom_site.label value
#
# row 3 should be siliently dropped, as all values are identical to row 1
# row 4 should cause a collision, as the values associated with the key are different
# row 5 should cause a collision, as the values associated with the key are different
#
# Dictionary: cif_core

data_block_A
loop_
  _atom_site.label
  _atom_site.type_symbol
  _atom_site.fract_x
  _atom_site.fract_y
  _atom_site.fract_z
  Na1  Na 0.0 0.0 0.0
  Cl1  Cl 0.5 0.5 0.5
  Na1  Na 0.0 0.0 0.0    # all values equal, silently drop
  Na1  O  0.25 0.25 0.25 # collision; not all values equal
  Na1  Na 0.0 0.0 0.00   # collision; not all values equal
